    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Investigate\r\n\r\nIt's important to make sure tracks have the same length when playing together. And we can even combine tracks that weren't part of the original song!\r\n\r\n1) Drag out another <code style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 148, 202); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play together</code> block and connect it underneath your code\r\n2) Drag out the <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone-stand\" style=\"color: #F99258; margin-right: 2px\"></i> So call me maybe </span> block\r\n3) Drag out 3 more <code style=\"background-color: rgb(116, 53, 178); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play</code> blocks and choose tracks from the Acoustic Arcade pack to play with it!\r\n\r\nPress the <code style=\"background-color: #fca401; color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px1 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">Run</code> button and listen to how your song sounds!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
